SECTOR-TYPES — All Sector Designations

  Use 'des <sects> <letter>' to change designation.
  Use 'resource *' to find the best sites for each type.

  KEY: Letter — Name (produces / consumes)

TERRAIN (cannot be changed):
  .   sea              (impassable by land, navigable by ships)
  ^   mountain          (impassable to land units; passively yields
                         gold dust — no civs/workers needed)
  -   wilderness        (unclaimed land, explore or build to claim)
  ~   plains            (same as wilderness; distinct terrain flavor)
  s   sanctuary         (deity-only; new player start zone before
                         a real capital is chosen)
  \   wasteland         (deity-only; nuclear fallout zone)

ECONOMIC — mines resource deposits (see 'resource *'):
  m   iron mine         (iron ore — needs high min resource)
  g   gold mine         (gold dust — needs high gold resource)
  u   uranium mine      (radioactives — needs high uran resource)
  a   agribusiness      (food — needs high fert resource)
  o   oil field         (oil — needs high ocontent resource)

ECONOMIC — manufacturing (consumes other commodities):
  j   light manuf       (LCM — consumes iron)
  k   heavy manuf       (HCM — consumes iron, at 2x the iron cost)
  d   defense plant     (guns — consumes oil, lcm, hcm)
  i   shell industry    (shells — consumes lcm, hcm)
  %   refinery          (petrol — consumes oil)
  b   bank              (gold bars — consumes dust)

ECONOMIC — nation-level output (consumes lcm; needs education >= 5
except library/park):
  t   tech center       (tech level — consumes dust, oil, lcm)
  r   research lab      (research level — consumes dust, oil, lcm)
  l   library/school    (education level — consumes lcm)
  p   park              (happiness level — consumes lcm)

ECONOMIC — no production:
  c   capital           (civilian happiness bonus, tax money;
                         cannot be redesignated away)
  n   nuclear plant     (no automatic production; used to build
                         nuclear weapons)

MILITARY:
  e   enlistment center (auto-recruits civs to mil each update)
  f   fortress          (defense bonus; full-speed land unit
                         efficiency build-up, like headquarters)
  !   headquarters      (defense bonus; full-speed land unit
                         efficiency build-up, like fortress)
  )   radar installation (sweep for ships/missiles with 'radar')

INFRASTRUCTURE:
  h   harbor            (ships built/docked here; 10x cargo
                         packing bonus)
  *   airfield          (planes built/based here)
  w   warehouse         (10x cargo packing bonus; storage hub)
  +   highway           (movement cost drops toward zero as
                         efficiency approaches 100%)
  #   bridge head       (land end of a bridge, on the shore)
  =   bridge span       (the bridge itself, crosses water)
  @   bridge tower      (submarine-proof bridge foundation)

